msgid "They would have continued to argue"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Yes. The situation between the children would have gotten out of hand. \n"
"These are all correct answers!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "They could have hurt each other in the argument"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Yes. The children could have gotten so upset that they would have hurt each other. \n"
"These are all correct answers!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f2_grandfather.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "@data.characters.f2_grandfather.name would have had to stop working in the garden"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f2_grandfather.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Yes. If @data.characters.f2_grandfather.name had kept quiet, he would have had to spend more time and energy trying to resolve the conflict. \n"
"These are all correct answers!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Here are three tips to give positive instructions that work."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "BE SPECIFIC"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Say the behaviour you want your child to do.\n"
"But before you do that, connect to them, so they are more likely to listen."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Use your child’s name to get your child’s attention. Go down to their level. Make eye contact.\n"
"\n"
"Then say exactly what you want them to do. For example: “Please take your shoes off when you come inside, dear”."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "BE REALISTIC"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Give one instruction at a time, and make sure that the instruction is something that your child can do. \n"
"\n"
"Giving a transition warning helps when you are asking them to change activities!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"It can be difficult for your child to remember many instructions, so only give one at a time!\n"
"\n"
"If possible, give a transition warning. For example: “In 10 minutes, you will need to pack away your toys so we can start getting ready for bed.”"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "BE POSITIVE"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Try using positive words when giving instructions. For example, instead of “Don’t shout inside” say “Talk in a quiet voice when we’re inside.” \n"
"\n"
"ALWAYS praise your child for following your instruction. Remember that this will make them more likely to repeat the behaviour you have just praised them for, and listen to you next time!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "More"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Give instructions in a firm voice and stay calm. Behave as if you expect your child to do what you ask.\n"
"\n"
"Praise, praise, praise! Make sure you praise your child immediately when they follow your instruction.\n"
"\n"
"Also, be kind to yourself if you forget sometimes. Learning how to give positive instructions is not easy, but it works!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "To practise giving instructions that work, let's try turning our negative instructions into positive ones."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Select each option to see how to turn it into a positive instruction:"
msgstr ""

